<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,222,751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
This is a relatively large genus of about 
<number box="[610,638,223,247]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="20.0">20</number>
species, restricted to the Afrotropical region. Due to the variability of species and the marked sexual dimorphism in some species, there has been considerable confusion regarding this genus in the past (
<bibRefCitation author="Riley" box="[358,489,294,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Riley, N. D. (1925) Notes on the genus Ceratrichia (Lep., Hesperiidae). Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 9, 16, 405 - 416. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222932508633328" type="journal article" year="1925">
Riley 
<number box="[429,489,294,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="1925.0">1925</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The treatments by 
<bibRefCitation author="Riley" box="[723,867,294,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Riley, N. D. (1925) Notes on the genus Ceratrichia (Lep., Hesperiidae). Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 9, 16, 405 - 416. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222932508633328" type="journal article" year="1925">
Riley (
<number box="[800,858,294,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="1925.0">1925</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[924,1078,295,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Evans, W. H. (1937) A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History), London, UK, 212 pp., 30 plates." type="book" year="1937">
Evans (
<number box="[1009,1069,295,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, however, have remained fairly stable for many years. 
<bibRefCitation box="[419,655,330,355]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Collins, S. C., Larsen, T. B. &amp; Warren-Gash, H. (2004) Notes on Afrotropical butterflies with the description of eleven new species and four new subspecies (Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera) - ABRI Research Paper No. 3. Metamorphosis, 14 (3), 63 - 110. [' 2003 ']" type="journal article">
Collins 
<emphasis box="[510,563,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[588,647,331,355]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
made some adjustments, and recently 
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen" box="[1109,1271,331,355]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2013) Ceratricula and Flandria - two new genera of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Hesperiinae (incertae sedis )) for species currently placed in the genus Ceratrichia Butler. Zootaxa, 3666 (4), 476 - 488. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.4.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Larsen (
<number box="[1204,1263,331,355]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
removed four species to his new genera 
<emphasis box="[443,574,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ceratricula</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[629,729,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Flandria</emphasis>
, for which there is no information on their early stages or food plants. 
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen" box="[236,398,403,427]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2013) Ceratricula and Flandria - two new genera of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Hesperiinae (incertae sedis )) for species currently placed in the genus Ceratrichia Butler. Zootaxa, 3666 (4), 476 - 488. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.4.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Larsen (
<number box="[331,390,403,427]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recognised four principal colour patterns of 
<taxonomicName box="[927,1058,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[927,1058,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ceratrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<taxonomicName box="[1135,1228,402,427]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis box="[1135,1228,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-, 
<taxonomicName box="[1256,1382,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phocion">
<emphasis box="[1256,1382,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. phocion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nothus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. nothus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-, and 
<taxonomicName box="[305,477,439,462]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrosticta">
<emphasis box="[305,477,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. argyrosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-groups), but found their genitalia very uniform. 
<taxonomicName authority="Joicey &amp; Talbot" authorityName="Joicey &amp; Talbot" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semlikensis">
<emphasis box="[1055,1325,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ceratrichia semlikensis</emphasis>
Joicey &amp; Talbot
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[238,294,474,499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis box="[238,294,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group) is treated below (
<figureCitation box="[588,689,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[150,1426,285,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[141,1426,285,1720]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Adults of Ceratrichia semlikensis, Kakamega Forest, Kenya. 1, at rest, 22 Sep 1991; 2, male sunbathing, 17 Jun 1991; 3, female sunbathing, 1 Jul 1990." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251869/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
Figure 
<number box="[673,689,475,499]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
), while living adult representatives of the three other groups are shown in 
<figureCitation box="[260,356,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,966,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,964,1953]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Adult Ceratrichia spp. 1 – 2, C. phocion, Forêt de Yapo, Côte d’Ivoire, 4 Dec 1988; 3, C. brunnea, Kakamega Forest, Kenya, 19 Jul 1990; 4, C. mabirensis, Kakamega Forest, Kenya, 31 Aug 1995." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251868/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
Figure 
<number box="[339,356,511,535]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[368,491,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phocion">
<emphasis box="[368,491,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. phocion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bethune-Baker" authorityName="Bethune-Baker" box="[505,806,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnea">
<emphasis box="[505,630,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. brunnea</emphasis>
Bethune-Baker
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[823,930,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nothus">
<emphasis box="[823,930,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. nothus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group), 
<taxonomicName authority="Riley" authorityName="Riley" box="[1028,1251,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mabirensis">
<emphasis box="[1028,1182,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. mabirensis</emphasis>
Riley
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1259,1427,511,534]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrosticta">
<emphasis box="[1259,1427,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. argyrosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- group).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,222,751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
No food plant records had been published, until 
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen" box="[744,902,582,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2005) Butterflies of West Africa. Vols. 1. &amp; 2. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, Denmark, 595 + 270 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Larsen (
<number box="[835,894,582,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported MJWC’s observation that 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semlikensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ceratrichia semlikensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
feeds on 
<taxonomicName box="[389,608,618,643]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Isachne" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis box="[389,608,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Isachne mauritiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[647,724,619,643]" name="Kenya" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Kenya</collectingCountry>
. No information is yet available for other species of the genus, but given that they usually fly low down along the edges of paths and streams with low grass or along forest edges (T.B. Larsen pers. comm. 
<number box="[456,515,691,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2014.0">2014</number>
, authors’ observations), it seems likely that they will also be found to be grass feeders.
</paragraph>
